<body>

    <h2> .:: TOTAL SURFACE AREA CALCULATOR ::. </h2>

    <p> 

Task 1. <br><br>

Write a program that calculates the Total Surface Area of a Cylinder. </p>

 <blockquote> formula: 2πr<sup>2</sup> + 2πrh </blockquote>

<p> Note: The input from keyboard (take π  = 3.142). <br> Where h = Cylinder height, r = radius

<hr>

 </p>

<script>

alert("A Program to calculate the Total Surface Area of a Closed Cylinder");

var π = 3.142;

var r = prompt("Enter radius (cm): ");
var h = prompt("Enter height (cm): ");

document.writeln("<h3> Data from User: </h3>"); 

document.writeln("Radius: " + r + "cm <br>"); 
document.writeln("Height: " + h + "cm <br>");

var A1 = 2*π*(r*r) ;

document.writeln("<h3> Calculation: </h3>"); 

document.writeln("<i> Taking π = 3.142 </i> <br>");
document.writeln("The Base Surface Area = 2 x 3.142 x " + r + "<sup>2</sup> = " + A1 + "cm<sup>2</sup><br>");

var A2 = 2*π*r*h ;
document.writeln("The Lateral Surface Area = 2 x 3.142 × " + r + " x " + h + " = " + A2 + "cm<sup>2</sup><br>");

var A = A1 + A2;

document.writeln("<hr color=yellow, width=60%><p id = 'p1'><b>The Total Surface Area of the Cylinder = Base Surface Area + Lateral Surface Area = </b></p>" + A + "cm<sup>2</sup> " );

</script>

<p>
<marquee><i> Refresh page to perform another calculation <i></marquee>
</p>

